Q1) Explain Type casting and its types with examples?
Ans - The procedure of converting one datatype into its equivalent another datatype is known as typecasting.
There are two type of typecasting-
i. Implicit typecasting (upcasting/widening)
ii. Explicit typecasting (downcasting/narrowing)

ex- int x=50;
    byte y=(byte) x;



Q3) Explain the difference between local and instance variables?
Ans - If a variable is inside a class it is known as instance variable and if a variable is
 inside a method it is known as local variable.
